dct_description_sm: Imprint derived from the earliest atlas in which the map was issued. Issued in this state in successive editions of the atlas until the plate was destroyed in 1672. Shows hundred boundaries, rivers, woods, parks and settlements ; college and university coats of arms. Relief shown pictorially. French text on verso with caption title: Oxford-shire; p. 177-178; signature Ggg; includes hand-colored illustration of Stonehenge.
